<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The Label decorator utilizes {{Zend_Form_Decorator_HtmlTag}} when {{$options['tag']}} is provided in order to wrap itself in the defualt tag {{dt}}. The call in {{Zend_Form_Decorator_Label::render()}} looks like this:</p>

<p>{{$decorator-&gt;setOptions(array('tag' =&gt; $tag, 'id'  =&gt; $this-&gt;getElement()-&gt;getName() . '-label'));}}</p>

<p>Because the parameters being passed to {{$decorator-&gt;setOptions()}} are hard-coded, with the exception of {{$tag}}, it makes it possible to set options besides tag and id (class for example) to the decorator. A fix might turn $tag into an array, something like this:</p>

<p>{{$this-&gt;addDecorator( 'Label', array( 'tag' =&gt; array( 'dt' =&gt; array( 'class' =&gt; 'myDtClass' ), 'class' =&gt; 'myLabelClass' ) );}}</p>

    </div>
</div>

